gomodel:SYNGO_5160  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: Depolarization-induced suppression of excitation was prolonged at climbing fibers-Purkinje cell and parallel fibers-Purkinje cell synapses in granule cell-specific and global monoacylglycerol lipase (aka. MGL, gene MGLL) knockout mice.\n\nFigure 5: Depolarization-induced suppression of inhibition was prolonged at stellate cells-Purkinje cell but not basket cell-Purkinje cell synapses in global monoacylglycerol lipase (aka. MGL, gene MGLL) knockout mice.. Experimental description: Result section, describing that mice were used in immuno EM: \"The density of MGL labeling was calculated as the mean number of metal particles per 1 μm2 of each element in wild-type and global MGL-KO mice. Statistically significant MGL labeling was found only in PF terminals and the BG (Fig. 1H).\"\n\nMGL antibody was produced at PMID:21613483\n\"For production of the MGL antibody, a cDNA fragment encoding the N-terminal 35 amino acids (NCBI reference sequence NM_011844) was subcloned into BamHI/EcoRI site of pGEX4T-2 plasmid (GE Healthcare) for expression of glutathione S-transferase fusion proteins.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5160" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

